  "body": "See here:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-03-24 16-39-57](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/159954533-15a16dc1-b2db-4a34-82af-f09768d9c16e.png)\r\n\r\nNotice how the chat toolbar in the top says \"Not a contact\".\r\nThen, notice how the modal of that contact has the option to \"Remove contact\".\r\n\r\nHere's how to reproduce this:\r\n\r\n1. Take any account on some public channel\r\n2. Right click -> Send message\r\n3. Then use toolbar to \"add to contacts\"\r\n4. Open modal again and see how it's actually added but still not updated in the toolbar\r\n",
